114
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:55,060
Next, let's welcome the class representative from Class 8.

115
00:06:57,670 --> 00:06:59,110
Principal. Principal, come here.

116
00:06:59,110 --> 00:07:00,980
Well... I'm sorry about this.

117
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:04,054
Our class representative is running over from the field.

118
00:07:04,054 --> 00:07:05,990
Look, there. He's on the field.

119
00:07:05,990 --> 00:07:08,233
How can he be late for this?

120
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:09,570
He's running over. Look, there he is.

121
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:11,820
- There. 
 - That one?

122
00:07:12,990 --> 00:07:14,720
Hurry up! Come on.

123
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:17,890
- Xuejiao! 
 - Isn't that Xuejiao?

124
00:07:17,890 --> 00:07:19,840
Xuejiao. Hurry up.

125
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,760
Hurry. Xuejiao.

126
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,530
Gu Xuejiao?

127
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:27,590
- This... why are you here? 
 - Sorry, Teacher.

128
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:29,940
Come here. Come on.

129
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,180
Come.

130
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:34,840
Come on.

131
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,430
- Xuejiao. 
 - Xuejiao.

132
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:41,330
- Come here. 
 - What's going on?

133
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:43,160
What's the matter with you?

134
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:46,570
How can a class representative show up late?

135
00:07:46,570 --> 00:07:49,412
- You forgot your watch? 
 - She...

136
00:07:49,412 --> 00:07:51,610
Wait, she... That...

137
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:53,760
Go and give your speech.

138
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,780
- Teacher, I... 
 - G-Go on then.

139
00:07:55,780 --> 00:07:57,720
Come up here.

140
00:07:59,790 --> 00:08:03,310
Let's welcome our Class 8 class representative to the stage!

141
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:04,360
Go, hurry.

142
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:06,330
- Go on. 
  - Yes! 

143
00:08:06,330 --> 00:08:07,710
Go, go, go.

144
00:08:07,710 --> 00:08:09,340
 Yes! 

145
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:17,060
   

146
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:30,090
Hello, everyone. I'm Gu Xuejiao from Senior Year, Class 8.

147
00:08:30,090 --> 00:08:31,380
 Great! 

148
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:33,650
Go, Xuejiao!

149
00:08:36,940 --> 00:08:40,200
My declaration for the college entrance exam...

150
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:43,540
is...

151
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:48,070
 I had to kick a contractor out to make room for you. 

152
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:49,500
 Although she's a contractor, she... 

153
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:55,420
She's passable, I guess, but can't compare to a real talent like you.

154
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:58,100
 You gave up everything for a guy, turning down promotion chances. 

155
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:01,240
 After five years, you're still a highly replaceable contractor. 

156
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:07,300
 If Yi Tianyu hadn't shown up, she might've gone to Jinghai University, not me. 

157
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:14,090
I want to go to Jinghai University!

158
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,280
♫  Block out the AC, sofa, and soft drinks  ♫

159
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:22,520
♫  Block out the games, TV, and posters  ♫

160
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,340
♫  Block out the yawning as a sign from heaven  ♫

161
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:27,950
♫  Block everything that is of no importance  ♫

162
00:09:27,950 --> 00:09:29,810
- What are you laughing at? 
 - What are you laughing at?

163
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:31,090
That's great!

164
00:09:31,090 --> 00:09:32,780
- Good! 
 - Xuejiao, you can do it!

165
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:34,140
Good!

166
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:35,180
Go!

167
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:36,480
Yes!

168
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,980
Go, Xuejiao!

169
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:40,000
- Xuejiao, go! 
 - Yes!

170
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,880
♫  Even if I fall, I fall with grace  ♫

171
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,080
♫  Whether life can be restarted   ♫

172
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,080
♫  I can't say for sure  ♫

173
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,420
♫  If I fail again, I won't be sad  ♫

174
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:47,880
You can do it!

175
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:50,640
♫  There is no secret manual to life, so let's ignite it  ♫

176
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,200
 - Yes. 
 - Jinghai University. 

177
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,390
 Yes, so? 

178
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:55,680
 Stop saying that. 

179
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:56,800
 He said it, not me. 

180
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:59,480
 - What did I say? 
 - Seriously? 

181
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:02,400
 What's wrong with Xuejiao wanting to get into Jinghai University? 

182
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,800
 I didn't say anything. 

183
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:06,990
 - Who said it? 
 - I heard you say it just now. 

184
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:22,100
I heard you're aiming for Jinghai University.

185
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:28,040
You're not talking about Jinghai Open University, right?

186
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:31,280
My dad said that it shut down years ago. Don't get scammed.

187
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,420
J, I, N, G, H, A, I.

188
00:10:33,420 --> 00:10:35,990
Also known as the "Dream School."

189
00:10:36,810 --> 00:10:38,700
You crossed the line.

190
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,110
Quiet! Quiet, please!

191
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:48,400
Class Representative, is your stomach better?

192
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,590
Cut it out. Don't mess around.

193
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:52,350
I've got real news.

194
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:55,040
The principal said all senior year students

195
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:57,550
will be having a parent meeting tomorrow afternoon.

196
00:10:59,230 --> 00:11:00,400
 It's that parent meeting... 

197
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,080
 He kept saying that after the meeting. 

198
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,960
 How could anyone resist it? 

199
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,830
 I was thinking, we did make money before by following his advice. 

200
00:11:06,830 --> 00:11:08,960
 Who would've thought it'd crash this bad? 

201
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,350
 Now look, we've put our savings in, 

202
00:11:11,350 --> 00:11:12,930
 as well as the borrowed money. 

203
00:11:12,930 --> 00:11:14,860
 What do we do now? How are we gonna live? 

204
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:16,240
 That so-called expert said, 

205
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:18,320
 "It has upside potential now. 

206
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:20,530
 Don't miss the opportunity." 

207
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:23,740
 Why did you believe everything he said? 

208
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:26,580
   

209
00:11:35,071 --> 00:11:37,060
What do you need?

210
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:38,560
I need you.

211
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:42,380
Hello, nice to meet you.

212
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:55,700
I saw you had a nightmare last time in the bookstore,

213
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:59,410
so I got you a protective doll.

214
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:07,630
Senior Brother Lin, please. Just take it.

215
00:12:07,630 --> 00:12:11,630
Maybe it'll help you ward off a big disaster.

216
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:14,510
This ugly doll will only give me more nightmares.

217
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,400
Don't listen to him. We won't listen to him!

218
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:20,292
I carefully selected this doll. It's both ugly and cute.

219
00:12:20,292 --> 00:12:22,340
How could you say that?

220
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,400
Senior Brother Lin.

221
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,270
You... I...

222
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:36,590
You're not giving me a doll for nothing. Just tell me.

223
00:12:36,590 --> 00:12:40,440
I... I... I just... I...

224
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:44,380
I just have a tiny little request.

225
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:52,000
Can you go to the parent meeting for me?

226
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,560
That's a tiny request?

227
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:58,510
Just this once! Please.

228
00:12:58,510 --> 00:13:01,920
Can you really bear to see me get scolded in front of the whole class by the teacher,

229
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:05,630
all helpless among a bunch of parents?

230
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:06,750
Yes.

231
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,060
And I'd enjoy it.

232
00:13:08,060 --> 00:13:09,630
Then...

233
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:12,990
Then all the more reason to see it in person.

234
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:14,680
I'm off.

235
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:16,320
Don't try to trick me.

236
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,870
I'm not going.

237
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:19,520
Look over there.

238
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:21,960
Senior Brother Lin! Please.

239
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:24,590
Tomorrow afternoon at 3:00. Okay? Please.

240
00:13:27,590 --> 00:13:30,120
- Here. 
 - Okay.

241
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,470
I heard someone in our class wants to go to Jinghai University.

242
00:13:36,470 --> 00:13:37,430
That's one ambitious goal.

243
00:13:37,430 --> 00:13:38,830
Hello, nice to meet you.

244
00:13:38,830 --> 00:13:39,990
I'm Yi Dafa.

245
00:13:39,990 --> 00:13:43,770
Big projects, no sweat, Yi Dafa's your bet!

246
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,350
We're all here thanks to fate.

247
00:13:49,350 --> 00:13:50,750
Right?

248
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:55,680
Through our kids... I'm in construction.

249
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:56,820
Here, older brother.

250
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:58,230
Here, little brother.

251
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:01,070
I'm in construction. Call me if you've got any projects.

252
00:14:02,470 --> 00:14:04,420
Uncle?

253
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:12,860
Dad!

254
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:16,180
I'm sorry, I made a mistake. I thought you were my dad.

255
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:18,990
Gu Xuejiao, since when were you nearsighted? Why didn't I know that?

256
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:20,700
I'm trying to get back to Class 1.

257
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,160
I've been studying too hard.

258
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,570
It's messing with my eyes.

259
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,870
 Weird. She's been all about studying lately. 

260
00:14:25,870 --> 00:14:27,040
 What's gotten into her? 

261
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:30,470
Xiao Gu, hello, I'm Tianyu's father, Yi Dafa.

262
00:14:30,470 --> 00:14:34,910
- Big... 
 - Big projects, no sweat, Yi Dafa's your bet!

263
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:37,870
What a great kid. This kid's going places!

264
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:39,040
Is this seat taken? Can I sit here?

265
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,910
Yes, you can.

266
00:14:43,470 --> 00:14:46,560
 Back in the day, whenever Yi Tianyu and I fought, 

267
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:49,630
 Uncle always had my back. 

268
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:53,290
 Uncle, you also had your glory days. 

269
00:14:57,180 --> 00:15:00,160
Xiao Gu, where are your parents?

270
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:03,040
My parents...

271
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:07,160
They've passed away?

272
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:09,360
Don't say that.

273
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,360
You...

274
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,560
Your dad looks so young!

275
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:28,920
I'm her uncle.

276
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,070
Biological uncle.

277
00:15:31,070 --> 00:15:33,200
Such a fine-looking uncle.

278
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,960
Here's my business card.

279
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,040
Yi Dafa.

280
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,590
Thank you.

281
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,350
What made you change your mind and come to my rescue?

282
00:15:42,350 --> 00:15:45,710
 Can you really bear to see me all helpless in front of the whole class? 

283
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:47,280
I couldn't bear it.

284
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:51,110
All right, parents, well, it's about time.

285
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:52,710
Please take your seats, okay?

286
00:15:52,710 --> 00:15:55,440
And students, please go out.

287
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,510
Come on.

288
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:57,710
Don't say nonsense.

289
00:15:57,710 --> 00:15:59,200
- Come on, hurry. 
 - Be nice.

290
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:01,140
Just wait to get scolded.

291
00:16:17,830 --> 00:16:19,800
Tianyu, let's go play ball.

292
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:20,920
No.

293
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,200
Why not?

294
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,110
I already brought the ball.

295
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:28,310
My dad still doesn't know what score I got last time.

296
00:16:28,310 --> 00:16:30,170
He should find out soon.

297
00:16:30,170 --> 00:16:32,760
What if he gets so angry that he has a stroke?

298
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:36,550
Okay, I'll keep an eye out for you.

299
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:44,132
 This parent meeting is actually... 

300
00:16:44,132 --> 00:16:45,550
Gu Xuejiao.

301
00:16:45,550 --> 00:16:47,030
What?

302
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:49,140
Let's take a look. Go.

303
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:50,990
 There's only one topic today, the college entrance exam. 

304
00:16:50,990 --> 00:16:54,440
The Study God from No.7 High School is actually your uncle.

305
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,990
And you didn't tell me?

306
00:16:56,990 --> 00:16:59,600
He's just a stand-in today.

307
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,000
You got someone to pretend—

308
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,410
 A few days ago, we already had our prep rally. 

309
00:17:05,410 --> 00:17:09,270
 Some students' goals are really ambitious. 

310
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,790
Others are more realistic.

311
00:17:10,790 --> 00:17:13,620
I believe you parents already have a clear sense

312
00:17:13,620 --> 00:17:16,030
of what schools to aim for.

313
00:17:16,030 --> 00:17:17,580
Right?

314
00:17:18,470 --> 00:17:19,990
What goals? With 300-something scores?

315
00:17:19,990 --> 00:17:22,360
So, today, if you have any questions,

316
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:24,550
I'm here to answer them. Okay?

317
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:27,270
Teacher, I heard someone in our class is aiming for Jinghai University.

318
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:30,580
Isn't that a bit much?

319
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:37,550
Having a major goal is already half the battle won.

320
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:38,640
Whose parent is that?

321
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,790
He looks so young.

322
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:47,250
I don't know if you've heard about the Zeigarnik Effect.

323
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:52,470
Those who have a big goal and are pushing forward towards it

324
00:17:52,470 --> 00:17:54,550
have a greater chance of success.

325
00:17:57,890 --> 00:18:00,310
So, I don't think it's laughable.

326
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:04,520
In fact, if every goal were easy to reach,

327
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:07,000
then life wouldn't be worth much.

328
00:18:12,470 --> 00:18:14,550
The Zeigarnik Effect.

329
00:18:14,550 --> 00:18:18,200
Whose parent is that? He's so eloquent!

330
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,350
Who's eloquent? Let's go.

331
00:18:21,180 --> 00:18:22,360
What about your dad?

332
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:23,550
Forget it.

333
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:26,360
I just remembered, last time he beat me like crazy without a break.

334
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,710
He's not going to have a stroke.

335
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:28,650
He's right.

336
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:30,790
Big dreams need a bold spirit.

337
00:18:30,790 --> 00:18:33,540
You need to aim high to reach high.

338
00:18:33,540 --> 00:18:34,890
I'm going to write it down.

339
00:18:34,890 --> 00:18:38,130
I think this parent made a very good point.

340
00:18:38,130 --> 00:18:39,960
We often say,

341
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,790
parents' support gives children the strength to go far.

342
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:45,640
 Parents' vision sets the child's horizon. 

343
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:48,440
 So, I think, it isn't necessarily a bad thing 

344
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,920
 to aim a little higher. 

345
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:53,790
Your daughter Shiyun got the highest score in English this time.

346
00:18:53,790 --> 00:18:55,400
She's so impressive.

347
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,880
What tutoring program is she in?

348
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,070
Her?

349
00:18:58,070 --> 00:18:59,640
She doesn't go to any tutoring classes.

350
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,510
We've never interfered in her studies.

351
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:03,510
It's all her own effort.

352
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,360
What a brilliant kid.

353
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,410
And she isn't just smart, she's pretty too.

354
00:19:07,410 --> 00:19:08,930
Of course, she takes after her mom.

355
00:19:08,930 --> 00:19:11,380
You flatter me.

356
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:12,710
Yunyun.

357
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:15,230
- Mom. 
 - We were just talking about you.

358
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:17,920
Were you helping the teacher again?

359
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:20,990
Okay, we'll leave you two to chat.

360
00:19:20,990 --> 00:19:23,300
- We'll leave first. 
 - Okay, see you around.

361
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:24,440
Bye-bye.

362
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,660
- Goodbye, Aunties. 
 - Goodbye.

363
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:32,160
Mom, I'm done with my things, too. Want to go home together?

364
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,400
Go home?

365
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:38,260
The gift for your teacher is in the car. Go and get it.

366
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:42,600
Out of all the subjects, only your English is decent.

367
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:45,390
All the money I spent on you was for nothing.

368
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,750
Shiyun.

369
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:05,160
So what do you think? Am I reliable?

370
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,230
What do you mean?

371
00:20:06,230 --> 00:20:08,960
That night, I helped cover for you and Xuejiao.

372
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:12,990
Seriously, it was a test of both physical and mental strength.

373
00:20:12,990 --> 00:20:15,160
I was running back and forth between two rooms

374
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:17,020
and switching between two genders.

375
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:21,510
You mean that night when Jiaojiao and I were together?

376
00:20:21,510 --> 00:20:22,970
Yes.

377
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:25,550
Is your mom done with the parents' meeting?

378
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:28,340
My mom actually asked me to tell her something.

379
00:20:29,470 --> 00:20:31,840
- Parents' meeting? 
 - You didn't know?

380
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:35,490
There was a meeting, but I'm in the repeaters' class.

381
00:20:35,490 --> 00:20:37,200
We didn't have one.

382
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,960
But the meeting for Class 8 should be over by now.

383
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,380
My mom should've left already.

384
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:44,270
Did your class's meeting run late?

385
00:20:44,270 --> 00:20:46,530
It wasn't the meeting.

386
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,970
It was my mom chatting with everyone.

387
00:20:49,970 --> 00:20:51,240
It took a while.

388
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,510
But can you blame her?

389
00:20:52,510 --> 00:20:54,210
Her daughter is doing so well,

390
00:20:54,210 --> 00:20:56,420
she must've been glowing with pride at the meeting.

391
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:59,760
Well, that's her glory. It has nothing to do with me.

392
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:01,440
Why would you think that?

393
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:04,950
You're amazing. Your mom should be proud of you.

394
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:10,710
Am I really amazing?

395
00:21:10,710 --> 00:21:14,180
If you aren't, then who else can be called amazing?

396
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:18,040
Then tell me, what's so amazing about me?

397
00:21:19,190 --> 00:21:22,150
You're pretty.

398
00:21:22,150 --> 00:21:23,820
And beautiful.

399
00:21:23,820 --> 00:21:25,060
Aren't those the same thing?

400
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:26,660
What else?

401
00:21:27,910 --> 00:21:29,990
And...

402
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:32,190
- And... 
 - Shiyun!

403
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:33,620
Why are you here?

404
00:21:33,620 --> 00:21:36,230
Your mom's looking everywhere for you.

405
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:37,780
Aren't you Xuejiao's brother?

406
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:38,850
What are you doing here?

407
00:21:38,850 --> 00:21:42,280
Why do you care? It's not like you own the place.

408
00:21:43,430 --> 00:21:45,260
Shiyun, is he your friend?

409
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:46,840
Not really.

410
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:53,530
Big dreams need a bold spirit.

411
00:21:53,530 --> 00:21:55,990
You need to aim high to reach high.

412
00:21:55,990 --> 00:21:58,730
- That's great. 
 - This is amazing.

413
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:00,830
This is awesome, really.

414
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:03,420
Xuejiao! You're back so early?

415
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,820
Yes. School let out early today.

416
00:22:05,820 --> 00:22:09,000
I also want to go to the bookstore to get some reference books.

417
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,310
Why did you suddenly buy a new computer?

418
00:22:11,310 --> 00:22:13,830
This is the cash cow for our family.

419
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:17,272
- Exactly. 
 - Are you guys...

420
00:22:17,272 --> 00:22:20,630
A while ago, Uncle Zhou recommended a promising stock.

421
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:21,760
We gave it a try.

422
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:24,830
We didn't expect it to keep climbing.

423
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:26,680
We withdrew all our money

424
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:29,240
and also borrowed 30,000 yuan from your Grandma. We put it all in.

425
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,080
   

426
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:40,260
What did you feed her? You gave her a stomachache.

427
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:43,550
Is this a happy face?

428
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:46,500
Yeah, what's with that face?

429
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:51,330
I mean...

430
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:59,690
 So, the stock expert is actually Zhou Shiyun's dad. 

431
00:22:59,690 --> 00:23:01,240
 I dodged the parent meeting, 

432
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:03,140
 but didn't see this coming. 

433
00:23:03,140 --> 00:23:06,575
 So, this is what "life never stops throwing curve balls at you" means? 

434
00:23:06,575 --> 00:23:07,720
 No. 

435
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,660
 There must be a way to fix this. 

436
00:23:14,420 --> 00:23:17,440
   

437
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:20,040
Even a dictation took that long?

438
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,920
   

439
00:23:28,315 --> 00:23:30,640
6003135.

440
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,760
There were plenty of good stocks. Why did they pick this one?

441
00:23:35,630 --> 00:23:38,120
 It's been crashing the whole time. 

442
00:23:38,670 --> 00:23:41,080
 We're so unlucky. 

443
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:44,390
 There's just one digit difference, just one. 

444
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:47,500
 6003135. 

445
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:49,680
 If I had known, I would've bought the neighboring stock, 

446
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:51,500
 and I would've made a fortune. 

447
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:54,310
 The crashing stock ends with 135. 

448
00:23:54,310 --> 00:23:57,770
 Then does the neighboring stock end with 134 

449
00:23:57,770 --> 00:24:00,400
 or 136? 

450
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,900
 It's all fate. 

451
00:24:07,499 --> 00:24:11,159
Is it 4 or 6?

452
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:13,550
It's 6.

453
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,910
With the fall of the six kings, the empire unified.

454
00:24:15,910 --> 00:24:17,250
The mountains in Shu were denuded, and the grand Epang Palace was built.

455
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:19,260
Over three hundred li it spreads, severing the sun from the heavens.

456
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:21,480
You can't even recite the first line.

457
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:25,337
Take the ginseng back, use it on yourself.

458
00:24:25,337 --> 00:24:27,630
I... I wasn't thinking about that.

459
00:24:27,630 --> 00:24:30,960
You really underestimate your own teaching skills.

460
00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:33,430
What were you thinking about?

461
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:34,670
You couldn't even tell 4 from 6.

462
00:24:34,670 --> 00:24:36,130
I...

463
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:41,520
I'm looking at this for my parents.

464
00:24:48,350 --> 00:24:50,300
First, rule out the one in the middle.

465
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,030
Why?

466
00:24:53,380 --> 00:24:56,940
This candlestick pattern clearly signals a drop.

467
00:25:00,570 --> 00:25:02,520
You know stocks?

468
00:25:03,730 --> 00:25:05,000
A little bit.

469
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,711
Then can you tell me which of these two

470
00:25:06,711 --> 00:25:09,701
shows signs of a big surge?

471
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,640
I can give you some info.

472
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:14,530
But don't chase the hype.

473
00:25:14,530 --> 00:25:16,160
Especially you. 
    

474
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,440
This one.

475
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,090
Just like that?

476
00:25:19,090 --> 00:25:20,860
Take it or leave it.

477
00:25:21,570 --> 00:25:23,640
The Epang Palace Rhapsody.

478
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,290
Like I'd believe you.

479
00:25:26,290 --> 00:25:28,160
Xiao Gu.

480
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:32,420
Uncle, what are you doing here?

481
00:25:32,420 --> 00:25:34,390
- What a coincidence. 
 - It sure is.

482
00:25:34,390 --> 00:25:37,860
I was just feeling lost, and then I saw you.

483
00:25:37,860 --> 00:25:40,900
Quick, help find some books for my son.

484
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:41,940
I have no idea.

485
00:25:41,940 --> 00:25:44,520
Your son?

486
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:46,740
Uncle, I'll be leaving first.

487
00:25:57,580 --> 00:26:00,290
Sorry about that. I just randomly recommended a few books.

488
00:26:00,290 --> 00:26:02,380
I didn't expect he'd buy them all.

489
00:26:02,380 --> 00:26:05,640
You know, even if you told him to buy all the books here,

490
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:07,430
he would've done it.

491
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:10,350
What about you? Can you read all these books?

492
00:26:10,350 --> 00:26:11,380
Read?

493
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:12,420
Why would I?

494
00:26:12,420 --> 00:26:14,500
They'll all be my table props.

495
00:26:15,860 --> 00:26:18,380
Xiao Gu, pick two more for him.

496
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:19,820
Money's not a problem.

497
00:26:19,820 --> 00:26:22,830
I just hope he can really learn a thing or two.

498
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:24,570
That's all I ask.

499
00:26:25,310 --> 00:26:27,040
I want to check out, please.

500
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,510
Hello.

501
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:30,820
Isn't this your uncle?

502
00:26:30,820 --> 00:26:32,800
You work here?

503
00:26:35,210 --> 00:26:36,900
He works part-time here.

504
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:39,890
He studies at Jinghai University, majoring in autonomous driving.

505
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:42,820
So? What's the big deal?

506
00:26:42,820 --> 00:26:45,050
That's very impressive. Very.

507
00:26:45,050 --> 00:26:46,840
- Brother Fa. 
 - Hurry and take a look.

508
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:48,410
Are we missing anything? Pick something out for us.

509
00:26:48,410 --> 00:26:49,670
You must know the best.

510
00:26:49,670 --> 00:26:52,470
You flatter me. Can he even finish all these?

511
00:26:52,470 --> 00:26:54,140
He'll have to.

512
00:26:57,710 --> 00:27:00,390
Give him an inch, and he takes a mile.

513
00:27:01,670 --> 00:27:03,230
- Here. 
 - Okay.

514
00:27:03,230 --> 00:27:05,080
Uncle and Xiao Gu.

515
00:27:05,080 --> 00:27:06,800
Thanks to both of you.

516
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:07,880
You helped me big time.

517
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,470
- Bye, Uncle. 
 - Okay.

518
00:27:09,470 --> 00:27:11,400
- Take care. 
 - Bye.

519
00:27:13,930 --> 00:27:16,920
They're also calling me your uncle.

520
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:19,810
When can we stop being relatives?

521
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:22,710
Soon.

522
00:27:22,710 --> 00:27:25,050
They're just being friendly.

523
00:27:28,270 --> 00:27:30,470
What's the deal with you and Yi Tianyu?

524
00:27:30,470 --> 00:27:31,610
What else could it be?

525
00:27:31,610 --> 00:27:33,470
We're just classmates.

526
00:27:33,470 --> 00:27:35,560
The college entrance exam is just around the corner.

527
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:37,180
Don't get distracted.

528
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:39,840
You have nothing to worry about.

529
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:42,160
